The paper discusses attribute-based access control, which is a topic related to security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Ethereum's smart contracts suggests a focus on distributed systems and blockchain technology (cs.DC). The implementation of the proposed scheme in Solidity indicates a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). The use of smart contracts to mediate interactions between different authorities and entities suggests a focus on database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the use of attribute-based access control in a decentralized society suggests a focus on cybersecurity (cs.CY).
